> 5" ?    Are you sure the timing isn't severely retarded?  I would advance
> the timing first. See what the vacuum is at 7.5 before TDC.
>
> You do not need to R&R the engine to remove a DP intake.  Just loosen the
> clamps on the boots, remove the carb, remove the left side intake end,
> remove the nut on the center support mount, then slide the center section
> out to the left.
